Package net.dean.jraw.http

Contains all the classes which directly build off of OkHttp

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    HttpAdapter<T>
    This interface provides a library-inspecific way of executing HTTP requests.
    HttpClient
    Provides a high-level overview of basic features of a HTTP client.
    NetworkAccessible
    Denotes that this class has the ability to send HTTP requests
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    BasicAuthData
    Represents a username and password to be used when executing a request using HTTP Basic Authentication.
    FormEncodedBodyBuilder
    Utility class to create RequestBody objects that are x-www-url-form-encoded.
    HttpLogger
    This class is responsible for logging objects relating to HTTP network activity, particularly the HttpRequest and RestResponse classes.
    HttpRequest
    This immutable class represents a HTTP request.
    HttpRequest.Builder
    This class provides an interface to create objects that model HTTP requests.
    MultiRedditUpdateRequest
    This class holds all the data necessary to create or update a multireddit.
    MultiRedditUpdateRequest.Builder  
    MultiRedditUpdateRequest.SubredditModel  
    OkHttpAdapter
    Provides a concrete HttpAdapter implementation using Square's OkHttp
    RequestBody
    Modeled after OkHttp's RequestBody class, but uses a Guava MediaType
    RestClient
    This class provides a high-level API to send REST-oriented HTTP requests with.
    RestResponse
    This class is used to show the result of a request to a RESTful web service, such as Reddit's JSON API.
    SubmissionRequest
    Models the parameters of a call to Endpoints.COMMENTS_ARTICLE
    SubmissionRequest.Builder  
    UserAgent
    This class represents the value of the User-Agent header.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    AuthenticationMethod
    A list of ways a client can authenticate themselves using Reddit's API
    HttpLogger.Component
    Represents the components involved in logging an HTTP request and response
    LoggingMode  
    MediaTypes
    A list of common MediaType objects used throughout the project
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    CheckedNetworkException
    A checked version of NetworkException
    NetworkException
    Thrown when an HTTP response is not successful
